  "prompt": "Is he still interested?",
  "response": "Determining whether someone is still interested in you can be challenging, especially without specific context. Here are a few signs to look for:\n\n1. **Communication:** Is he initiating conversations or responding promptly and enthusiastically to your messages?\n2. **Time and Effort:** Does he make time to see you or spend quality time together?\n3. **Engagement:** Is he attentive during conversations and genuinely interested in your life?\n4. **Future Plans:** Does he talk about or make plans for the future with you?\n5. **Body Language:** If you're in person, does he maintain eye contact, lean in, or show other positive body language cues?\n\nIf you're noticing a lack of these behaviors, it might be a sign that his interest has waned. However, the best approach is to have an open and honest conversation with him to clarify where you stand. Sometimes people go through busy or stressful periods, which can affect their behavior, so direct communication is key.",
